    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="393"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/1310</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala (<persName type="from"
                            >Donald</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 716</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-28">July 28,
                            1932</date>.<lb/>[Received August 6.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the American Vice
                    Consul in Puerto Barrios<note n="27" xml:id="d393fn27">
                        <persName corresp="#p_PPJ1">Patrick J. Powers</persName>.</note> has advised
                    the Legation that the Guatemalan engineers for the aerial survey of the disputed
                    territory, <persName corresp="#p_SL2">Lisandro Sandoval</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_BMA1">Miguel Angel Balcárcel</persName>, with the Chief of
                    Protocol, <persName corresp="#p_SLD1">Delfino Sanchez-Latour</persName>, arrived
                    at Puerto Barrios on July 23rd. The Honduran engineers, <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZVM1">Medardo Zuñiga-Vega</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CSF1">Felix Canales-Salazar</persName>, arrived by airplane from
                    Tegucigalpa on July 24th. The American <pb facs="0482" n="378" xml:id="pg_378"/>
                    engineers, <persName corresp="#p_BSH1">Sidney H. Birdseye</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_HV1">Vincent Hanrahan</persName>, arrived on July
                    25th. On July 26th, all of the engineers went to Bananera on an inspection trip.
                    The Vice Consul reports that he is advised that they will work between Puerto
                    Barrios and Gualan from the railway line towards the border.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">G. K. Donald</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
